<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dixie Union Wins Norfolk Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Dixie Union, ridden by Alex Solis, went  
wide on the turn and still overtook Forest Camp in the stretch for 
a half-length victory Sunday in the $200,000 Norfolk Stakes at 
Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
	Dixie Union covered the mile on the turf in 1:35.79.  
</P>
<P>
	Forest Camp, who took the lead soon after the start but was  
passed by Dixie Union near the sixteenth pole, finished four 
lengths in front of Anees. New Advantage, Slayton and Radix Alis 
completed the order of finish in the race for 2-year-olds. 
</P>
<P>
	The Kentucky-bred Dixie Union, trained by Richard Mandella,  
earned $120,000. 
</P>
<P>
	This was Dixie Union's first race around two turns. His first  
loss in four tries was to Forest Camp in last month's Del Mar 
Futurity, where he lost by five lengths. 
</P>
<P>
	Dixie Union paid $10.40, $2.40 and $2.10. Forest Camp returned  
$2.10 and $2.10, while Anees paid $2.10 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
