	Chechen Leader Proposes Peace Plan  
</P>
<P>
	GROZNY, Russia (AP) -- Chechnya's President Aslan Maskhadov  
outlined a peace plan Sunday to end the fighting in his breakaway 
republic, and promised to crack down on renegade warlords if Russia 
withdraws its troops from Chechen territory. He called on Russia to 
immediately end ``all combat actions,'' and said the two sides 
should observe the basic principles of a peace accord that ended 
the 1994-96 Chechen war. Russia did not respond immediately but was 
expected to reject several of Maskhadov's keys points, including 
the withdrawal of Russian forces. 

</P>
