Telegraph reported. Speaking on condition of anonymity, an Israeli 
official confirmed the report and said 400 immigrants arrived more 
than a year ago and have been living in the southern coastal city 
of Ashkelon. Cuba has no formal ties with Israel, having broken off 
relations after Israel's victory in the Yom Kippur War in 1973, so 
