<HEADLINE> Blues 4, Oilers 2 / Hockey Game Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EDMONTON, Alberta (AP) -- Geoff Courtnall's tie-breaking goal at  
15:19 of the third period lifted the St. Louis Blues to a 4-2 
victory over the Edmonton Oilers on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	St. Louis center Pierre Turgeon became the 55th NHL player to  
reach 1,000 points with a power-play goal at 13:23 of the second 
