<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Broncos' Sharpe Fractures Collarbone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Denver tight end Shannon Sharpe fractured  
his left collarbone late in the third quarter of Sunday's game 
against the Oakland Raiders, adding to the Broncos' long list of 
serious injuries this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Sharpe, who has gone to seven consecutive Pro Bowls and is tied  
for first among NFL tight ends with three 1,000-yard receiving 
seasons, was hit by two defenders and landed hard on the ground as 
he attempted to catch a pass from Brian Griese. 
</P>
<P>
	Sharpe, who has seven straight 50-catch seasons, was unable to  
hold on to the pass and had to be helped off the field. 
</P>
<P>
	The Broncos already are missing running back Terrell Davis and  
linebacker John Mobley for the season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
