<HEADLINE> Cathay To Lease Jets From Air China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HONG KONG (AP) -- Hong Kong-based Cathay Pacific Airways  
announced Sunday that it has signed an agreement to lease three 
Airbus A340-300 aircraft from Air China to meet growing demands on 
its key international routes. 
</P>
<P>
	An airline statement said the leased aircraft will begin service  
within the next two months. 
</P>
<P>
	Cathay Pacific has 11 A340s, which are generally used on  
long-haul destinations such as Auckland in New Zealand, San 
Francisco and Zurich. 
</P>
<P>
	With the addition of the new Airbus aircraft, Cathay Pacific  
will have a fleet of 62 planes, including 19 Boeing 747-400s, the 
statement said. 
  	   	
</P>
