<P>
                              *STATS   	
</P>
<P>
	The Tennessee Titans survived an NFL record for penalty yardage  
in beating Baltimore 14-11. Tennessee (4-1) won its 10th straight 
AFC Central Division game despite being penalized 15 times for 212 
yards. The previous record was 209 yards by Cleveland against the 
Chicago Bears in 1951. ... Junior Seau had 12 tackles and two of 
San Diego's six sacks in a 20-10 victory over Detroit. ... Kicker 
Phil Dawson scored expansion Cleveland's first rushing touchdown on 
a fake field goal attempt in the first quarter of the Browns' 18-17 
loss to Cincinnati. ... Kansas City's 16-14 victory over New 
England left the AFC with no unbeaten teams. 

</P>
