</P>
<P>
	Dallas had won 10 straight NFC East games and led 10-0 in the  
fourth quarter before losing 13-10 to Philadelphia on the Eagles' 
first offensive touchdown in 19 quarters, a 28-yard pass from Doug 
Pederson to Charles Johnson with 1:07 left. . ... Kordell Stewart, 
who went into the game with one touchdown pass and 11 interceptions 
in his last eight starts, had two TD passes and one interception in 
a 24-21 loss to Buffalo. ... Kurt Warner's 14 TD passes in two 
games is two more than the St. Louis Rams had all of last season. 
... Drew Bledsoe threw nine straight incompletions but was 9-of-11 
in a late New England comeback that fell short in a 16-14 loss to 
Kansas City. ... Arizona QB Jake Plummer did not throw an 
interception after he had 13 in the first four games. ... 
Baltimore's Errict Rhett, who came in as the AFC's leading rusher 
with three straight 100-yard rushing games, managed only 59 yards 
on 21 carries in a 14-11 loss to Tennessee. ... Denver held 
Oakland, which entered the weekend with an NFL-best 148 yards per 
game on the ground, to 55 yards rushing in a 16-13 victory. 

</P>
