<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> N.Korea Denounces U.S. Missile Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEOUL, South Korea (AP) -- North Korea denounced the United  
States on Sunday for testing a defense missile system over the 
Pacific, and vowed to build up its own defense capabilities. 
</P>
<P>
	``This (the test) shows that the U.S. policy to stifle North  
Korea has not in the least changed,'' said a commentary in Rodong 
Sinmun, a newspaper for the ruling Workers' Party. 
</P>
<P>
	``We will build our defense capabilities with high vigilance  
against the perfidious acts of the U.S.,'' it said. The report was 
carried by the North's official foreign news outlet, the Korean 
Central News Agency. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. Air Force earlier this month launched an unarmed  
missile and destroyed it with an interceptor rocket over the 
Pacific in its first test of a proposed missile defense system. 
</P>
<P>
	The system is designed to destroy missiles launched by rogue  
states or terrorists. Western countries, including the United 
States, have suspected North Korea, Iran and Syria of developing 
long-range missiles capable of hitting the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	But the North Korean commentary said Pyongyang was only trying  
to defend itself, whereas Washington was ``the aggressive force 
trying to hurt North Korea.'' 
</P>
<P>
	North Korea rattled nerves in Asia last year when it fired a  
long-range missile over Japan. This summer, the United States, 
Japan and South Korea feared that the North would test a new 
missile capable of reaching Alaska or Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
	The United States lifted some restrictions last month on trade,  
travel and banking in the reclusive communist country. In response, 
North Korea said it would freeze test-launches while its government 
negotiated with the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	Late last month, though, North Korea said it would still  
test-launch a missile if necessary. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
