<HEADLINE> 6 Students Hit By Truck and Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Six college students getting out  
of their cars or walking along a highway on their way to a 
fraternity party were killed early Sunday by a pickup truck whose 
driver who had fallen asleep, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident happened just after midnight about two miles west  
of the Texas A&AMP;M University main campus, said police Maj. Mike 
Patterson. 
</P>
