	The victims -- four students from Baylor University, one from  
Texas A&AMP;M and one from Southwest Texas State -- were among a group 
of people who were going to a party at the Tau Kappa Epsilon house 
along a four-lane highway. Some had just parked on the road 
shoulder and the pickup sideswiped two parked cars and struck a 
third. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses said parties at the fraternity often draw large crowds  
of people who must park on the shoulder of the highway, which has a 
65-mph speed limit. 
</P>
<P>
	The man driving the pickup, also a Texas A&AMP;M student, had just  
taken his girlfriend home and was returning to campus when he fell 
asleep and veered off the road, Patterson said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We could hear screaming and stuff but at first we didn't have  
any idea he was running over people,'' said Daniel Lara, a 
22-year-old student who lives next door to the fraternity. ``We 
walked out and saw bodies all over the place.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Their shoes were in perfect place from where they were  
walking,'' said Arissa Hill, a Blinn College freshman who was going 
to the party. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver, 18-year-old Texas A&AMP;M student Brandon Kallmeyer, was  
not injured and apparently had not been drinking, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Patterson said investigators will present evidence to Brazos  
County prosecutors without recommending charges. 
</P>
