<HEADLINE> Burn 2, Mutiny 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Jason Kreis scored in 82nd minute Sunday  
night to give Dallas a 2-1 victory over the Tampa Bay Mutiny, 
giving the Burn second place in the MLS' Western Conference. 
</P>
<P>
	Dante Washington also scored for Dallas (19-13), which will have  
home-field advantage in their upcoming conference semifinal series 
against the Chicago Fire. 
</P>
<P>
	Manny Lagos scored for the Mutiny (14-18), who finished third in  
the Eastern Conference. Tampa Bay will face the Columbus Crew in 
the opening playoff round. 
</P>
<P>
	Kreis, the MLS scoring champion, tied D.C. United's Roy Lassiter  
for the league lead in goals with his 18th from 10 yards out. 
</P>
<P>
	Washington gave the Burn a 1-0 lead from 15 yards in the 16th  
minute. Dallas appeared to get a break on the goal after replays 
showed Washington may have been offside on the play. 
</P>
<P>
	Lagos got the equalizer in the 71st minute, scoring from 10  
yards after pulling off some nifty footwork to get around 
goalkeeper Matt Jordan. 
</P>
<P>
	The Burn were without starters Ariel Graziani (Ecuador) and  
Jorge Rodriguez (El Salvador) due to national team commitments. 
Tampa Bay's Raul Diaz Arce, who has 13 goals, also missed the game 
to play for El Salvador. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas' Sergi Daniv did not play because of a knee injury.  
  	   	
