<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stars 3, Sharks 2 / Hockey Game Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Pavel Patera and Jere Lehtinen each  
scored goals in the final 5:40 as the Dallas Stars beat San Jose 
3-2 Saturday night, snapping the Sharks' season-opening three-game 
winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
	Rebounding from a 3-0 loss at Anaheim Friday night, the Stars  
finished up their road trip with their fourth win in five games 
this season. 
</P>
<P>
	With 5:40 remaining, Patera converted Dallas' go-ahead score,  
streaking into the slot to knock in a rebound from a shot by Mike 
Keane. 
</P>
<P>
	Less than 1 1/2 minutes later, the Stars went up 3-1 when Lehtinen  
picked up a loose puck and skated in to beat goaltender Steve 
Shields from up close. 
</P>
<P>
	San Jose pulled back to within one when Owen Nolan scored his  
sixth goal of the season. Nolan, who has at least one goal in his 
first four games, wristed a shot past goaltender Manny Fernandez 
with 2:49 left. The Sharks pulled Shields and added an extra 
attacker with 52 seconds but Fernandez fended off San Jose's late 
flurry. 
</P>
<P>
	Trailing 1-0, San Jose evened the score with 4:30 remaining in  
the second when Stephane Matteau ended a scramble in front of the 
net with his second goal of the season, sending the puck through 
goaltender Fernandez's legs. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas came out strong, outshooting San Jose 16-6 in the first  
period and scoring on a power-play goal by Jamie Langenbrunner. He 
was positioned by the left post and redirected a shot from Derek 
Plante into the net past Shields. 
</P>
<P>
	The Stars had a go-ahead goal disallowed with 11:34 left in the  
second. Shields fell into the net after blocking a second straight 
shot, loosening it from its moorings an instant before Brad 
Lukowich chased the rebound down and sent it back toward the net. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
