	Police in Howard County, a wealthy suburb of Baltimore and  
Washington, D.C., found the number of red lights run at four 
intersections dropped 57 percent five months after cameras were 
introduced last year. At one intersection, collisions dropped from 
15 in 1997 to eight last year. 
