<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Industrial Area to Double </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMMAN, Jordan (AP) -- Jordan's largest duty-free industrial zone  
plans to double its capacity to meet demand from customers in the 
United States and Europe, an official said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Al-Hassan Qualified Industrial Zone comprises 83 companies  
and factories, employing 5,000 people. It will double its size 
early next year to keep up with customer requirements, QIZ 
director-general Mohammed Itmeh said. 
</P>
<P>
	The zone, located 54 miles north of the capital, Amman, near the  
city of Irbid, was established two years ago by Jordan-Israel joint 
ventures. Its products are exempt from U.S. taxes and customs 
duties. 
</P>
<P>
	Itmeh said that last year the QIZ exported and sold goods worth  
$507 million, 60 percent of which was sold to U.S. and European 
markets. Its products are mainly clothes, food, textiles, 
engineering goods, plastic, rubber, chemical products, and luggage. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
