<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Garciaparra Late Addition to Lineup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Red Sox manager Jimy Williams arrived at Fenway  
Park on Sunday, thought about a lineup and decided to leave injured 
Nomar Garciaparra out of it. 
</P>
<P>
	Then Garciaparra showed up, tested his bruised right wrist and  
decided he could play against Cleveland, after all. So Williams 
wasted little time making room in his lineup for the AL batting 
champion. 
</P>
<P>
	``All I know is, he came into my office and said he was ready to  
play,'' Williams said. 
</P>
<P>
	So he put Garciaparra at shortstop and removed backup Lou  
Merloni, who was due to bat sixth. Garciaparra took his usual 
cleanup spot, and first baseman Mike Stanley was dropped to sixth. 
</P>
<P>
	Boston lost the first two games of the best-of-5 division series  
with Garciaparra. He went 2-for-3 with a homer in Game 1 but was 
0-for-3 in Game 2. 
</P>
<P>
	The Red Sox avoided a sweep with a 9-3 win Saturday . Merloni,  
who spent most of the season at Triple-A Pawtucket, went 2-for-3 
with a run and an RBI. 
</P>
<P>
	Garciaparra, hurt when hit by a pitch by Baltimore's Al Reyes on  
Sept. 25, led the AL with a .357 batting average. 
</P>
<P>
	The Indians ``have to think about'' pitching against  
Garciaparra, Boston second baseman Jose Offerman said. ``It's 
something they were talking about yesterday when they found out he 
wasn't in the lineup.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Williams didn't put him in it originally.  
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't want to put a lot of added pressure on this kid,''  
the manager said. ``The trainer taped his wrist and he went out the 
tunnel, and after he got done hitting, he came back and said he 
could play. So I changed the lineup.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Williams wasn't worried that Garciaparra might sustain  
additional damage. 
</P>
<P>
	``If there was any doubt in my mind that I'd be hurting this  
kid,'' Williams said, ``then I wouldn't put him in there in the 
first place.'' 
</P>
<P>
	There was little news about the condition of Boston's other  
star, Cy Young Award shoo-in Pedro Martinez. He stopped throwing 
after about one minute before Saturday's game after experiencing 
discomfort from a strained muscle beneath his right shoulder blade 
that he hurt in the opener. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams preferred to focus on Sunday's game rather than look  
ahead to a possible fifth game in Cleveland and whether Martinez 
could pitch in it. 
</P>
<P>
	``That's all I can focus on,'' Williams told reporters. ``When I  
was a little kid, I liked to play marbles. A lot of you people 
think I've lost mine. I don't know. I still got them at home in a 
big old brandy snifter. I really do.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Garciaparra missed the last five regular-season games after  
playing in the opener of a doubleheader at the Chicago White Sox in 
which Boston clinched the wild-card berth. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
